The general rule and its HC-NIC Page 40 of 49 Created On Sun Aug 13 23:05:35 IST 2017 exceptions has been reiterated in so many judgments of this Court, viz., U.P State Sugar Corpn. v. Sumac International Limited [1997] 1 SCC 568; State of Maharashtra v. National Construction Co. [1996] 1 SCC 735;
United Commercial Bank v. Bank of India [1981] 2 SCC 766 and Centax [India] Limited v. Vinmar Impex Inc. [1986] 4 SCC 136, that in U.P. State Sugar Corpn. v. Sumac International Ltd. (1997) 1 SCC 568 (hereinafter U.P. State Sugar Corpn.) this Court, correctly declare that the law was 'settled'.
